│ THOUGHT: The miscompile occurs when IPSCCP replaces FCmp with a constant during simplifyInstsInBlock. A safe fix is to modify tryToReplaceWithConstant to skip replacing    │
│ FCmp results under dynamic denormal mode, preventing incorrect folding like turning a non-splat vector compare into a splat(true). I'll insert a guard in                   │
│ tryToReplaceWithConstant: if V is an FCmp and the parent function’s denormal mode Input or Output is Dynamic, do not replace with a constant.                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ nl -ba llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SCCPSolver.cpp | sed -n '1,120p' && sed -n '1,120p' llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SCCPSolver.cpp | grep -n "bool                               │
│ SCCPSolver::tryToReplaceWithConstant" && awk 'BEGIN{print "Applying patch..."}' && cat <<'SED' > /tmp/guard_fcmp_try_replace.sed                                            │
│ /^bool SCCPSolver::tryToReplaceWithConstant(Value \*V) \{/a\                                                                                                                │
│   \ \ // Avoid replacing FCmp with constants under dynamic denormal mode.\n  \ \ // Respect \"denormal-fp-math\"=\"ieee,dynamic\" to prevent miscompilations.\n  \ \ if     │
│ (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {\n  \ \ \ \ if (I->getOpcode() == Instruction::FCmp) {\n  \ \ \ \ \ \ const Function *F = I->getFunction();\n  \ \ \ \ \ \ if (F) {\n │
│ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ DenormalMode Mode = F->getDenormalMode(APFloat::IEEEdouble());\n  \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ if (Mode.Input == DenormalMode::Dynamic || Mode.Output ==                 │
│ DenormalMode::Dynamic)\n  \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ return false; // Skip constant replacement for FCmp\n  \ \ \ \ \ \ }\n  \ \ \ \ }\n  \ \ }\n                                  │
