│ THOUGHT: The miscompile occurs when IPSCCP replaces an FCmp with a constant, ignoring "denormal-fp-math"="ieee,dynamic". A conservative fix is to prevent                   │
│ tryToReplaceWithConstant from replacing FCmp results with constants when the function’s denormal mode is dynamic, which avoids incorrect folding like splatting true for    │
│ non-splat vector compares.                                                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ perl -0777 -pe 's/bool SCCPSolver::tryToReplaceWithConstant\(Value \*V\) \{\n/bool SCCPSolver::tryToReplaceWithConstant(Value *V) {\n  // Avoid replacing FCmp with         │
│ constants under dynamic denormal mode.\n  // Respect \"denormal-fp-math\"=\"ieee,dynamic\" to prevent miscompilations.\n  if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {\n    if │
│ (I->getOpcode() == Instruction::FCmp) {\n      const Function *F = I->getFunction();\n      if (F) {\n        DenormalMode Mode =                                           │
│ F->getDenormalMode(APFloat::IEEEdouble());\n        if (Mode.Input == DenormalMode::Dynamic || Mode.Output == DenormalMode::Dynamic)\n          return false; // Skip       │
│ constant replacement for FCmp\n      }\n    }\n  }\n/' -i llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SCCPSolver.cpp && submit-patch                                                          │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                         │
